modules.description: This module handles network communication over TLS for IRC clients. It provides functions to establish secure connections to IRC servers, send and receive encrypted messages, and manage socket-level interactions. It works with IPv4/IPv6 addresses as strings and TLS client configurations.

This module implements secure IRC client functionality with TLS, providing functions to connect to servers, authenticate, and send IRC commands like JOIN, PRIVMSG, and PONG. It works with TLS-secured connections, string-based IRC messages, and structured configurations for addresses and keepalive settings. Concrete use cases include building bots that connect to IRC servers over encrypted channels, automatically reconnect on failure, and handle incoming messages through event-driven callbacks.
